<item>
            <title>[JXPATH-114] node() implementation in DOM and JDOM model</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JXPATH-114</link>
                <project id="12310480" key="JXPATH">Commons JXPath</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I think that the code in DOMNodePointer.java, line 120 is wrong because considers only element and document to be matched by node().&lt;br/&gt;
while instead it matches any node that pass from there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;case Compiler.NODE_TYPE_NODE :&lt;br/&gt;
                    return nodeType == Node.ELEMENT_NODE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt; nodeType == Node.DOCUMENT_NODE;&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;should be changed to &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;case Compiler.NODE_TYPE_NODE :&lt;br/&gt;
                    return true;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Same in JDOMNodePointer, line 391&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;                  return true;//(node instanceof Element) || (node instanceof Document);&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
